By Laura Schulte September 28, 2020

Trump misses the mark with claim that Green New Deal proposal wants to ban cows

    If Your Time is short

     * President Donald Trump claimed during a Sept. 17, 2020 rally in
       Mosinee, Wisconsin, that the Green New Deal calls for banning cows --
       “Cows are out … They don’t want cattle, they don’t want cows.” 

     * There is no mention of cows in the actual text of the proposal.

According to a Feb. 12, 2019 examination of the Green New Deal by
   PolitiFact National, there is no actual mention of cows in the deal’s
   text.

Our ruling

   Trump claimed that the Green New Deal, proposed by liberal Democrats,
   among other things aims to ban cows: "Cows are out … They don’t want
   cattle, they don’t want cows."
